This project implements a console-based conversational chatbot using a pre-trained transformer model (DialoGPT) from the Hugging Face library. The chatbot accepts user input, processes it using natural language generation techniques, and produces meaningful responses while maintaining conversation context. It utilizes tokenization, context handling, and sampling methods like top-k and top-p to generate dynamic replies. The system runs in a continuous loop, enabling interactive communication until the user exits. This project demonstrates the practical application of transformer-based models in building intelligent conversational AI systems.
